data.description: Welcome to 35 Central Avenue. This charming 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath colonial is the one you've been waiting for. Nestled at the end of a peaceful dead-end street, this 1800 square feet home offers spacious and comfortable living. On the first floor you will find the living room which is perfect for relaxation, with a cozy gas fireplace and built in speakers, a formal dining room, ideal for hosting gatherings and special occasions, an eat in kitchen with a large pantry and recessed lighting, an updated half bath and a bonus room which could be used as a den, family room or playroom. Upstairs, you'll find four generously sized bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. The primary suite is a true retreat, featuring a private en-suite bathroom. The remaining three bedrooms are versatile and can be customized to suit your needs, whether you want additional bedrooms, a home office, or a fitness space. The private outdoor space is fully fenced, with a garden, shed and above ground pool. The large screened in porch offers additional square footage and a fantastic place for barbecues or simply enjoying the beauty of your surroundings. Located only minutes from the Beach, the NYC Ferry, train, & GSP.
